CS 1.1 (Performance)
80% of database searches will return results on the screen in less than two seconds.

CS 1.2 (Capacity)
At most one client must be able to connect to the server (on the same machine).

CS 1.3 (Capacity)
The database will be capable of storing 100 audio elements.

CS 1.4 (Interoperability)
The system shall be written in Java.

CS 1.5 (Interoperability)
The client should be able to add new audio files in the data system.

CS 1.6 (Interoperability)
All configuration data shall be stored in XML files.
